" Type :help nv for help.

""""""""""""""""""""""
" < Clipboard
""""""""""""""""""""""
" yank to system clipboard
" set via setting: "vintageous_use_sys_clipboard": true,
" set clipboard=unnamed

" show register (i.e., clipboard history)
nnoremap <C-y> :reg<CR>

" Y consistent with D and C to the end of line
nnoremap Y y$

" always paste what was yanked (y), not what was deleted (d or c)
nnoremap P "0p

" stop polluting the register
nnoremap dd "_dd

""""""""""""""""""""""
" < Search
""""""""""""""""""""""
" search w/o having to press enter
set incsearch
set ignorecase

" no modifier key for jumping to next word
nnoremap + *

" quicker find mode (by mirroring American keyboard layout on German keyboard layout)
nnoremap - /

" [M]ute search highlights
nnoremap M :nohlsearch<CR>

""""""""""""""""""""""
" < Nagivation
""""""""""""""""""""""

" Have j and k navigate visual lines rather than logical ones
nnoremap j gj
nnoremap k gk
vnoremap j gj
vnoremap k gk

" HJKL behaves like hjkl, but bigger distance (best used with scroll offset plugin)
nnoremap H ^
vnoremap H ^
nnoremap L $
vnoremap L $
nnoremap J 6j
nnoremap K 6k

" no modifier key on German keyboard
nnoremap , ;

" Hard Mode: Turn off arrow keys for learning
" needs a remap, since unmap does not work on
" builtin keys, "noop" being non-existent command
nnoremap <Right> :noop<CR>
nnoremap <Left> :noop<CR>
nnoremap <Up> :noop<CR>
nnoremap <Down> :noop<CR>
vnoremap <Right> :noop<CR>
vnoremap <Left> :noop<CR>
vnoremap <Up> :noop<CR>
vnoremap <Down> :noop<CR>

" Goto Mark: remapping since ` not working
nnoremap Ã¶ `

""""""""""""""""""""""
" < Indentation
""""""""""""""""""""""

" Make indention work like in other editors
nnoremap <Tab> >>
nnoremap <S-Tab> <<
vnoremap <Tab> >gv
vnoremap <S-Tab> <gv

""""""""""""""""""""""
" < Jumps
""""""""""""""""""""""
" older
nnoremap Ã¤ <C-o>

" newer
nnoremap Ã„ <C-i>

""""""""""""""""""""""
" < Editing
""""""""""""""""""""""

" backspace works in normal mode like in insert mode & consistent with <Del>
nnoremap <BS> h"_x
nnoremap <S-BS> "_x
vnoremap <BS> "_d

" don't save small deletion in the register
nnoremap x "_x

" allows Double Enter to add new line and indent
nnoremap <CR> A

" Undo/Redo consistently on one key
noremap U <C-r>

" Change Word/Selection
nnoremap <Space> "_ciw
vnoremap <Space> "vc
" Delete Word/Selection
nnoremap <S-Space> "_daw
vnoremap <S-Space> "vdv

" Karabiner: <M-Space> = <PageUp>
nnoremap <PageUp> yiw
" Karabiner: <Fn-Space> = <PageDown>
nnoremap <PageDown> viwp

" Abolish: Titlecase
nnoremap Ã¼ crt
nnoremap Ãœ ~h

" transpose characters, consistent with Emacs/Mac
" already done built-in in Sublime
" nnoremap <C-t> xph

" Adding Blank Line above/below
nnoremap = mzO<Esc>`z
nnoremap _ mzo<Esc>`z

""""""""""""""""""""""
" < Text Objects
""""""""""""""""""""""
" mnemonic: [p]andoc citation syntax
onoremap pp i]

" mnemonic: [Z]iting someone
onoremap zz i"

""""""""""""""""""""""
" < Insert Mode
""""""""""""""""""""""
" implemented via in "Default (OSX).sublime-keymap"
" since neovintageousrc cannot do that in its rc file

""""""""""""""""""""""
" < Switch Modes
""""""""""""""""""""""
" implemented via preference 'vintageous_i_escape_jj'
" inoremap jj <Esc>
" rnoremap jj <Esc>

vnoremap J <Esc>
" already built in: press v in visual mode to go back

""""""""""""""""""""""
" < Surround
""""""""""""""""""""""
" emulate some smarter punctuation bindings from Smarter MD Hotkeys
nnoremap <C-5> ysiw]
nnoremap <C-8> ysiw)
nnoremap <C-2> ysiw"

